bug.short_desc: [abrt] ristretto: rstto_file_get_display_name(): ristretto killed by SIGSEGV
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Description of problem: 1. run ristretto (do not open a file, just run the command without arguments) 2. no image is shown up 3. pres the Delete key on the keyboard
OR
1. open a image file in ristretto 2. keep deleteting all images with the Delete key until no image is shown 3. press the Delete key once more
Expected: nothing should happen
Actuall: SIGSEGV
Version-Release number of selected component: ristretto-0.8.0-2.fc23
Additional info: reporter: libreport-2.6.4 backtrace_rating: 4 cmdline: ristretto '/home/churchyard/Sta\xc5\xbeen\xc3\xa9/13691171_284755561875417_154071991353796893_o.jpg' crash_function: rstto_file_get_display_name executable: /usr/bin/ristretto global_pid: 9353 kernel: 4.5.7-200.fc23.x86_64 runlevel: N 5 type: CCpp uid: 1000
Truncated backtrace: Thread no. 1 (2 frames) #0 rstto_file_get_display_name at file.c:321 #1 cb_rstto_main_window_delete at main_window.c:3313
Potential duplicate: bug 1289509

As far as I know, this is present in all the releases. I moved the version to 25 just to be safe.
Thanks for the report and upstream report. I am also able to reproduce this.
